I just got home not long ago and nobody was home. So I take off my clothes and start to cook up some bagel bites. My mom wasn't home so I was pretty happy that I had the house to myself. Everything was going pretty swell, but then my mom had called. Shes in the San Jose Animal hospital right now with my dog Ewok. Turns out, that my dog was a victim of a hit and run. My mom had taken him outside for a short moment, and she remembered that she needed to get something in the house. While she was in the house, she had heard a extremely loud "BOOM" and a very high pitched scream. Kinda like a yelp of pain, or just a shriek. She went outside at that moment, and she saw my dog laying on the road. She was horrified at the scene; by this time the car had already driven away. So as of now, my dog can't move or do anything. Im not sure whats gonna happen now, but I wish those people who hit my dog AND DROVE OFF get what they deserve.
